Summarise data from a timed_df to a timeseries

Source: R/timeseries.R
time_summarise.Rd

Summarise data from a timed_df to a timeseries

time_summarise(timed_df, ..., .fill = list())

Arguments

timed_df

a line list of data you want to summarise by the time column. If this is grouped the grouping is preserved and converted into a class column in the output. Ff the timed_df has a class column that is used in preference.

...

a spec for a dplyr::summary(...) - optional, and if not provided a count = dplyr::n() or a count = sum(count) is performed.

.fill

a list similar to tidyr::complete for values to fill variables with

Value

a timeseries dataframe, by time

Examples

library(tidyverse)
library(growthrates)

# a timed_df object:
tmp1 = tibble(
    time = floor(runif(100, 0, 20)),
    value = rnorm(100)
  ) %>%
  as.timed_df(days_in_period=7,start_date="2020-01-01")
# defaults to `count = n()`


tmp1 %>% time_summarise()
#> # A tibble: 20 × 3
#>    time       count date

# class grouping example

tmp2 = tibble(
    mygroup = c(rep("g1",50),rep("g2",50),rep("g1",50),rep("g2",50)),
    myclass = c(rep("a",100),rep("b",100)),
    time = floor(runif(200, 0, 20)),
    value = rnorm(200)
  ) %>%
  group_by(mygroup) %>%
  as.timed_df(days_in_period=7,start_date="2020-01-01",class_col=myclass,grp_label = "{mygroup}")
#> classes defined: class=myclass
#> groups defined (mygroup): group=`{mygroup}`

tmp3 = tmp2 %>% time_summarise()
tmp3 %>% restore_groups()
#> # A tibble: 80 × 5
#>    mygroup myclass time       count date      
#>    <chr>   <chr>   <time_prd> <int> <date>    
#>  1 g1      a       0              5 2020-01-01
#>  2 g1      a       1              1 2020-01-08
#>  3 g1      a       2              3 2020-01-15
#>  4 g1      a       3              1 2020-01-22
#>  5 g1      a       4              2 2020-01-29
#>  6 g1      a       5              1 2020-02-05
#>  7 g1      a       6              3 2020-02-12
#>  8 g1      a       7              6 2020-02-19
#>  9 g1      a       8              1 2020-02-26
#> 10 g1      a       9              2 2020-03-04
#> # … with 70 more rows


tmp4 = tmp3 %>% time_decompose()
tmp4 %>% restore_groups()
#> # A tibble: 200 × 3
#>    mygroup myclass time      
#>    <chr>   <chr>   <time_prd>
#>  1 g1      a       0         
#>  2 g1      a       0         
#>  3 g1      a       0         
#>  4 g1      a       0         
#>  5 g1      a       0         
#>  6 g1      a       1         
#>  7 g1      a       2         
#>  8 g1      a       2         
#>  9 g1      a       2         
#> 10 g1      a       3         
#> # … with 190 more rows
